specs.implementationPlan:
All hooks already exist; the Design commands currently fall through to the generic "notImplemented" dropdown. Add real handlers in commands.js (object `H` / dispatch), CSS classes in editor.css, and small flyout CSS.

1) STYLE SET MODEL (commands.js): define an ordered array of style sets, each `{ id, name, cls }` where cls is the body class applied to #editor (e.g. id:'word', name:'Word', cls:'' for default; 'lines-distinctive' -> 'ss-lines-distinctive'; etc.). Use the 18 confirmed names; you may ship a working SUBSET of ~8-10 with distinct CSS (Word(default), Basic (Simple), Basic (Elegant), Lines (Simple), Lines (Distinctive), Shaded, Casual, Centered, Minimalist, Black & White (Word)) and still list the rest mapping to the nearest implemented look so the gallery is complete. Store current set id on WC.Editor (e.g. E().styleSetId) and persist via the existing dirty/serialization path if documents are saved (apply class to #editor; serialize by also writing the class onto the saved root — check files.js/getHTML; simplest: keep it as a document-level setting saved alongside HTML, or write the class on a wrapper). 

2) APPLY (commands.js `H.styleSet`): open WC.flyout(node, ...) building the `.styleset-gallery` grid from the array. applySet(id) = remove all `ss-*` classes from E().node, add the chosen one (skip for default 'word'), set E().styleSetId, mark dirty, E().repaginate(); E().updateStatus(); E().emit(). Hover handlers: previewSet(id) on mouseenter (apply class without committing), and on mouseleave/flyout-close restore the committed set. Add separator + 'Reset to the Default Style Set' (applySet('word')) + 'Save as a New Style Set...' (WC.toast honest stub). Because the ribbon control type is "gallery" with cmd `styleSet`, add `if (cmd==='styleSet') return styleSetMenu(node);` in Commands.dropdown AND ensure Commands.run routes the gallery click to it (gallery type isn't split/dropdown, so add `H.styleSet = (c,node)=>styleSetMenu(node);`). 

3) CSS (editor.css, new "Design — Style Sets" section): one block per set overriding the existing heading rules, e.g.
   #editor.ss-lines-distinctive h1, #editor.ss-lines-distinctive h2 { border-bottom: 2px solid var(--heading-color); padding-bottom: 3pt; }
   #editor.ss-lines-distinctive h1.doc-title { border-bottom: 3px solid #156082; }
   #editor.ss-shaded h1, #editor.ss-shaded h2 { background: #156082; color:#fff; padding: 3pt 6pt; }
   #editor.ss-centered h1, .ss-centered h2, .ss-centered h3, .ss-centered .doc-title, .ss-centered .doc-subtitle { text-align:center; }
   #editor.ss-minimalist h1, .ss-minimalist h2 { text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.06em; font-weight:600; color:#595959; }
   #editor.ss-casual .doc-title { font-size:32pt; } #editor.ss-casual h1 { color:#156082; font-weight:700; }
   #editor.ss-basic-elegant h1, .ss-basic-elegant h2 { font-family: Cambria, Georgia, serif; font-style:italic; }
   #editor.ss-bw-word h1, .ss-bw-word h2, .ss-bw-word .doc-title { color:#000 !important; }
   Use the existing THEME accent vars/THEME_COLORS for colored sets. Keep specificity equal to the base `#editor h1...` rules (already `#editor h1`) so the class-qualified rules win by source order — put the Style-Set block AFTER the base heading rules (lines 107-114).

4) PARAGRAPH SPACING (commands.js `H.paragraphSpacing`): flyout listing the 6 presets with the verified after/line values; applyPreset = iterate E().node block-level children (or all p/li/h*) setting style.marginBottom + style.lineHeight (or apply at document level by setting CSS vars + a `ps-*` class on #editor mirroring the Style-Set approach — cleaner & undo-friendly). Active preset tracked on E(). 'Custom...' -> WC.Dialogs.paragraph(). Use document-level class approach: `#editor.ps-open p{margin-bottom:10pt;line-height:1.15}` etc., so it composes with Style Sets.

5) EFFECTS (commands.js `H.effects` + dispatch `if (cmd==='effects') return effectsMenu(node);`): flyout of theme-effect names; selecting one -> WC.toast('Theme Effects change how shapes, SmartArt and charts render their fills, lines and shadows. This clone draws simple shapes, so the effect set is recorded but has limited visible impact.') and store E().themeEffects = name. Honest stub, but it opens a real, named gallery rather than notImplemented.

Files to edit: /home/ogutd/msword-clone/src/renderer/js/commands.js (add H.styleSet, H.paragraphSpacing, H.effects + 3 menu builders + dispatch lines), /home/ogutd/msword-clone/src/renderer/styles/editor.css (Style-Set + Paragraph-Spacing class blocks), optionally /home/ogutd/msword-clone/src/renderer/styles/ribbon.css (.styleset-gallery/.ss-cell flyout grid styling). ribbon-data.js already has the controls/items — no change needed except optionally bumping feasible from "partial" to "yes" for styleSet/paragraphSpacing. Persistence: if files.js serializes #editor.innerHTML only, also save E().styleSetId/psId/themeEffects (e.g. as data-* on a wrapper or in the saved doc metadata) so reopened docs keep their look.
